caption: Awesome place! Espresso made to perfection and their quiches are amazing. Trendy inside and very nice service.
One of my favorite places for breakfast in downtown Chicago
Food was great! So grateful we found this space.... definitely adding it to our regular spots to visit downtown! Everything was so fresh and delicious!
Get the prosciutto and brie panini. You wont regret it!
Amazing Cakes! I had a German chocolate cake and cheesecake.  They were amazing!
Nice cafe
Fabcakes is a neighborhood favorite! Their homemade pastries are out of this world, and I get coffee there every morning! Fabiola is the sweetest small business owner, go support her!

I just went here today for the first time and had the homemade almond mocha syrup latte and a homemade chocolate banana Fabcake. Both were phenomenal and I’ll be going back for more! I recommend supporting this small business! You can tell that the owner really cares about the product and experience she is providing to her guests. Enjoy your coffee and treats here!
Cute little place. Great prices for the amount served. Some tables inside were open. Fast service. Great tasting coffee and breakfast bagel.
I ate the Chocolate Espresso scone and I'm pretty sure I saw God

I had a Dulce de Leche coffee and was awesome...
Great food Great atmosphere
Best pastries in the city

When I first walked in I noticed how dimly lit the cafe was, and the red fabric againist the walls that resemble curtains on a stage. I ordered the vanilla rose latte and it tasted great. The rose flavor could've been a tad stronger, it was more of a slight taste that it's there.  but I like the prominence of the espresso. There wasn't much of a selection on the bakery side, probably because I came during the opening, so they were still working on getting the goods out.  Overall, I will definitely come back to try some of the other lattes. The cafe is a bit dark and dim and kind of depressing to be a study spot. So this is more of a pickup and go for me.
Good food, good people, and Fabcakes!
Fantastic breakfast sandwiches!!
Baked avocado eggs! 🤤
Correction to review, thought it was Firecakes. Fabcakes has Good coffee, tea, pastries. Nice place to meet with someone or bring your laptop.
Fabulous Cakes.... for sure.
Didn't try their coffee yet, but their panini and other sandwiches are great.
Always pleasant and delicious
I go nearly every day to enjoy the variety of pastries and baked goods along with an excellent array of coffee. Plus the staff is great.
The salted Nutella cookie is fantastic!
Have only been here once for a smoothie, walked past it with a friend of mine and decided to give it a shot. The smoothie was great and I'll have to come back to try the other options.
Really good food! Totally recommended
Mocha was good. They clearly use a nice dark chocolate and not the cloyingly sweet syrup that some places use. The bagels are okay.
Great coffee!

Man, I am not sure where to begin. Let's start with the Lavender Latte - the whole reason why I came to this place today. Either your lavender syrup is so bland or badly made that when the barista put it in my latte it tasted like slightly bad nothing - or your girl never put it in. Which is a shame, since I made the trip for it. Strike 1. I also treated myself to a quiche - big mistake! I can't believe I have to explain to you how to bake your own goods but heres a tip: UM Crusts need a binding agent 🤷‍♀️ cause if you leave it out, your customers will take one bite and then the whole thing will crumble and turn to dust. I had to throw it away because i literally couldnt eat it - it was a goupy dust pile.  Its been a while since ive been in this shop so maybe your having a bad day. Or maybe your standards have lowered. But for me - you haven't given me a reason to return. Money down the drain.
Best breakfast bagel I had in Chicago. Amazing scones. Croissants that are authentic and are generous with the chocolate.
Love the Fabcakes, love the coffee, love the staff!
Really good food, friendly staff and nice atmosphere.
nice place to have a rest and a cup of coffee and energy. Service is really warm, food is beyond average.
Good but slightly overpriced
On the days they make gluten free treats, they are absolutely amazing.  Their coffee is good to.  Great place to destress. Great ambiance.
Great cozy place for breakfast or lunch. Not fancy but "homey". Homemade deserts!
Neighborhood coffee and muffins

I've visited Fabcakes twice for breakfast and I crave the Bagel with Lox regularly.  The overall menu doesn't have a lot of options, but is varied enough to accommodate virtually everyone. I also enjoy the lattes and most recently discovered my new favorite, the Aztec Latte.  This is a cozy place with plenty of outlets to charge up or plug in, ample seating and a friendly staff.

This place came highly recommended by a friend of mine. I wanted a comfortable laid back place with a comfy decor, good food and good drinks. It also had ro have a decent amount of gluten free foods available as well. ( celiac )  This place fits the bill. I walked in and immediately felt right at home. The red curtained walls and hanging art work really add its subtle opulence. But as always, its the staff that can really make or break a place. Emma is so friendly and outgoing. She treated *every single guest*  with the same amount of appreciation and respect. I was there for a while, so I got to sample a few things on the menu: The chicken salad on GF toast is served with lettuce and tomato and has a nice little spicy bite to it. I also had the potato quiche.  It was so good I bought an extra for my breakfast tomorrow. Decent prices too. You'll love it here.
Really cozy coffee shop
Love this place!
Great food and friendly service
Such an underrated place. Excellent food and pastries.
I can't believe I have walked by this place everyday and never stopped in! Breakfast sandwich and cappuccino are amazing. Cute place. Good to grab and go. Or sit with a book or computer.
All the food is good.  Scones best.
A good coffee shop with excellent baked goods

By far my favorite cafe in the city! The people that work here are incredibly kind and helpful. I’ve tried many of the specialty lattes and the vanilla rose is my favorite. That latte and a prosciutto panini is my usual order. The lox that they offer for bagels comes in a hefty portion and tastes fresh. The pastries are absolutely delicious and never taste hard or stale! There is usually plenty of space to sit down and get some work done. I highly recommend taking the CTA or walking due to the fact that street parking is ridiculously expensive.
Scone was flaky, decently moist, and tasty.
Always a great selection of house made baked goods.  Serves Ipsento coffee. Made to order sandwiches,  panini, salads. Great service. Good environment for working or meetings.

If you have time, stop in for a wonderful breakfast or lunch.  They make their pastries from scratch.  The sandwiches, soups and coffee are fantastic!  Did I mention that the owner and employees are friendly too?  Love this place!

Cool vibe and kind servers. Good spread of menu items but not particularly cost effective. However, it fits the price range of the area. It also had ample seating and employees don't hassle you about sticking around for a while. Makes a great place to get some work done in a relaxed environment.

The coffee is always on point, their food is delicious and healthy, and the service never fails! they're always friendly and very professional. This is exactly how you run a coffee shop, great job to the entire crew!
I am a regular. Food is on healthier side. One of THE BEST bakery items are made here!!
Great sandwiches and lattes. Good fast service even during morning rush. Right off the brown line
Great coffee!! Why this doesn't come up when I search for coffee is a mystery. Great little shop. Baked goods, nice people.
I always get the Lavender Latte. Highly recommend this place. And great prices too!
Great place for a coffee during the workday. Quiet enough for a conversation.
Great service, good food, and cozy!
Really good latte and smoothies. The pastries are also really good and fresh. Fast, friendly service.
I recommend trying the Hawaiian Panini. It's like a fresh mini pizza on bread

First off, for some reason I thought this was a donut shop. I was wrong. However, they sell delicious scones and cakes. I got the mix fruit crumb cake and a mix fruit scone, both of them were delicious. The seats are good enough, but the laid-back atmosphere here is awesome. Great for getting some work done and getting a good cup of coffee.
Good service. Welcoming environment. Great place to get work done or have a conversation. Tea and pastries are great, however, the coffee is not good.
Wonderful Space. Undiscovered as a study area.
One of my go to coffee shops in River North
Really good coffee but not the coziest of interiors.
There Fab Latte is fantastic as well as there Caprese Sandwich
love it
The food was tasty, and the service was excellent. I forgot to pick up a pastry I had ordered before leaving, and a staff member came outside to bring it to me!
Great for business meetings. Good coffee, quiet atmosphere, not a lot of seating.
This place is so great. We had coffee, kids, food and hung out for a long time without 'bothering' staff.
Great quick local spot for bagels, sandwiches, coffees and pastries. Veggie friendly as well!
Really good food and coffee. Try the Aztec latte, it's delicious (and contains Mexican chocolate). They have breakfast and lunch food primarily. Hot. All good.

We were underwhelmed with our experience here. The coffee was standard, and the cookies that my wife and I got were "ok" but nothing special. We wanted to be blown away, but instead we were ready to move on and do something else. It was entirely forgettable, which is unfortunate because we'd heard such great things. Maybe we'll give it another try the next time we're in town and get something different....
Great service, delicious quiche. I love good knowledgeable friendly service.
Great coffee shop, drop in for a great experience.
Cozy place, very friendly staff and the best scone I've ever had.  Best lavender  latte too. Our family wants to come back for an afternoon snack and for tomorrow's breakfast!
Nice, yummy place for sweets and coffee or tea.
There are some unusual coffee flavors but good. Their pastries are pretty good too
We loved everything we tried - their doughnuts, cakes, paninis, lattes.
Wonderful coffee. Many different kinds.
I'm here since a few time.  The food was delicious all the time, I tried sweet and salty stuff. Staff is very friendly. I love this place. ❤️
Nice little coffee shop. They also have decent sandwiches and muffins.
Comfortable place, smooth lattes.

We often stay in River North on trips to the Lyric Opera and this is always a must-visit stop for us. The coffee drinks are great (particularly the specialty lattes - lavendar and pepper fig are really notable).  But for me the draw is the fabulous baked goods selection. EVERYTHING is amazing and the hardest part is always deciding which of them to have. If you want a great coffee drink along with some of the best baked goods you will ever have, along with good (though sometimes overworked) service, this is the place.  I should also mention that this place brings a very nice European ambiance to the area.

omg. I pass this place all the time on my way to work.  It doesn't look like much on the outside so I never went inside nor had the desire. One day I'm again passing it on my way to work and decided to be spontaneous and go inside. The inside looked clean and tiny. When I glanced at the menu however, I was inlove. The food here is great, and the staff if warm. I think this is an amazing hole in the wall and I'm so glad I came in. My favorite item is the House flatbread, consisting of pear, arugula, goat cheese, honey, prosciutto and truffle oil. Hell yes. I also love the Lavender Latte. Really good. As far as the drinks go price - wise comparable to Stabrucks. I think the place is quite affordable and just great for a light breakfast or light lunch.

I had a vanilla rose latte here and it was one of the best espresso beverages I've ever experienced! I'm glad it consumed it inside despite the weird patio furniture and red curtains used for decor - I love their big mugs! They didn't offer a full breakfast menu, but the pastries looked fresh and tasty!
good god, y'all....incredible

I really like this bakery/cafe nestled between the art galleries on Wells St. The high ceilings and big windows help the relatively narrow space feel bigger than it really is, and it usually stays pretty quiet during the day. On my most recent visit, I got the Nutella cheesecake and it was effing delicious. Plus they have a cute little aquarium by the bakery case so you can check out the fish if you get tired of drooling over the pastries and muffins. If you're in the neighborhood, it's definitely a better bet than Starbucks.

The desserts here are simply amazing! The ambience is terrific and the staff is super friendly! Love coming in here and trying really bizarre and amazing desserts! Way better than a Starbucks and more relaxed and quiet.
Awsome food and great costumer service. It is a great place to grab a snack or get breakfast. I totally recommend it! Hats off to Tyler our very  pleasant server.
Excellent place to go to for lunch! I love everything about them. Everything.

Such a cute place. I went for a lunch since I work nearby and was pleasantly surprised. They have salads, sandwiches and great deserts. I had the house specialty "zapiekanka"- face up baked sandwich- delicious. I also tried an almond late and was better than the some of the more popular late's I am used to.

FabCakes is a fun addition to the neighborhood. It is a small place but has plenty of seating. All of the food looks delicious. I have had their smoothies which are made with fresh fruit, milk and juice. They taste great and are a relatively healthy snack. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable. If you are in the area I highly recommend FabCakes!
Despite the fluffy name, Fabcakes is a great place to grab a tea, coffee or smoothie with your click mate. Their pastries and cookies are amazing so don't leave without splitting one!

This is one of my favorite places to grab a cuppa joe, a great bagel, pastry, you name it. I found this place because of a deal website and I just keep coming back. The atmosphere is very European, the staff is so nice. #30daychallenge
